  "prompt": "What is a recipe like Whole Foods mock chicken salad?",
  "response": "Here's a recipe similar to Whole Foods' mock chicken salad:\n\nIngredients:\n- 2 cans (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and mashed\n- 1/2 cup vegan mayonnaise\n- 1/4 cup diced celery\n- 1/4 cup diced red onion\n- 2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley\n- 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 teaspoon dried dill\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Optional: 1/4 cup chopped almonds or cashews for crunch\n\nInstructions:\n1. Drain and mash chickpeas with a fork or potato masher\n2. Mix in mayonnaise, celery, red onion, parsley, mustard, and dill\n3. Season with salt and pepper\n4. Add optional nuts for extra texture\n5. Chill for at least 30 minutes before serving\n6. Serve on bread, in a wrap, or on top of greens\n\nThe key is to make it creamy and flavorful while using chickpeas as a plant-based protein substitute for chicken.",
